                                        We are limited in providing details of Horseman’s Funds to investors who are not Professional Investors. In the UK you must be a Professional Client (as defined in the UK Financial Conduct Authority  (”FCA”) Rules) or for potential non-UK investors you otherwise are permitted to receive Fund details  pursuant to local private placement requirements.
                                        Where you have not fallen under the Professional Investor definition you may wish to elect to opt-up Elective Professional Client status. 
                                        


                                        Do you wish to elect to be treated as an Elective Professional Client? This may permit access to Horseman Fund details, depending upon your jurisdiction and you having sufficient knowledge and understanding of the nature of and risk inherent in unregulated Funds. If you elect to do this you will lose certain regulatory protections that you would otherwise have as a Retail Client.
                                    

